    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-04-17T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-04-17T05:00:00-05:00" n="163"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d163">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.60p2/32: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Latvia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Coleman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Riga</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-04-17T12:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 17, 1928—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received April 17—9:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>35. Department’s instruction No. 415, February 17, 1927,<note n="47"
                        xml:id="d163fn47">Not printed; it transmitted the President’s full power
                        authorizing Minister Coleman to sign the treaty.</note> regarding proposed
                    commercial treaty with Latvia.</p>
                <p>Full accord now reached with Latvian Government on all points and final draft
                    proposed by Foreign Office ready for signature in Legation’s possession. Request
                    immediate telegraphic authorization to sign.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Coleman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
